Britain's Prince Harry, Duke of Sussex (R), and his wife Meghan, Duchess of Sussex, pose for a photo with their newborn baby son, Archie Harrison Mountbatten-Windsor. JOHANNESBURG - Prince Harry celebrated his first Father's Day, just over a month after welcoming baby Archie Harrison with wife Meghan Markle. In honour of the special day the royals posted to their Sussex Instagram account a picture of their baby boy's face. READ: Prince Harry, Meghan Markle celebrate Pride Month "Happy Father's Day! And wishing a very special first Father's Day to The Duke of Sussex," the caption reads. The royal bundle of joy, Archie Harrison Mountbatten-Windsor, was born on 6 May. Happy Father’s Day! And wishing a very special first Father’s Day to The Duke of Sussex © SussexRoyal A post shared by  The Duke and Duchess of Sussex (@sussexroyal) on Jun 16, 2019 at 5:01am PDT